## Setting Up Your Environment ğŸ–¥ï¸
To get started with JavaScript:
1. Open **Google Chrome** (or any modern browser).
2. Open Developer Tools (Right-click > Inspect > Console).
3. Type `console.log('Hello, JavaScript!');` and press **Enter**.

---
## JavaScript Basics ğŸ“š
### 1. Variables & Data Types
Variables store data values. In JavaScript, you can declare variables using:
```js
let name = "Alice"; // String
const age = 25; // Number
var isLearning = true; // Boolean
```

### 2. Functions
Functions are reusable blocks of code.
```js
function greet(name) {
    return "Hello, " + name + "!";
}
console.log(greet("Alice"));
```

### 3. Conditionals
Execute different code based on conditions.
```js
let score = 90;
if (score >= 80) {
    console.log("You passed! ğŸ‰");
} else {
    console.log("Try again! âŒ");
}
```

### 4. Loops
Repeat actions multiple times.
```js
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    console.log("Iteration: " + i);
}
```

